comment.text:
This comment applies to trunk version

This can be controlled via configuration (eg web.config):
<monorail>
    <url useExtensions="false" />
or in code:
public void Configure(IMonoRailConfiguration configuration)
{
   configuration.UrlConfig.UseExtensions = false; 
}

That said I think that if the configured extension in an empty string than no dot should be added regardless if the user forgot the set useExtensions="false".

What does someone else thinks?
